<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="199" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="70.[166,794,1573,1713]" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[166,271,1573,1597]" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Remarks</emphasis>
. Vijayiines are mostly a free-living deep-water group. Except for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1904" box="[385,562,1603,1626]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Vijaya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuipes">
<emphasis box="[385,562,1603,1626]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Vijaya tenuipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and one species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andres" authorityYear="1981" box="[166,334,1632,1655]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Pseudamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[166,334,1632,1655]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Pseudamaryllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the vijayiines have been found in the deep seas of the North and South Atlantic Oceans, the Red Sea and western South Pacific Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
